The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Eight corporate teams will take part in the Pankaj Roy 20/20 tournament at the BF Block Park, Salt Lake. The meet, being organised by the Pankaj Roy Cricket Academy, will be held over four weekends beginning Sunday. Announcing this at a press conference Thursday evening, Pranab Roy informed that the final will be held on March 26. 

 The eight teams ? HSBC, CitiBank, TCS, Eforce, Skytech, Ladvantage, IBM and Chembiotech ? will be divided into two groups. The top two from each group will advance to the semis. While the winners will receive the Pankaj Roy Cup, the runners-up will get the Ambar Roy Cup.

 Powered by Satyen Bhattacharya?s 97, Aryan defeated Burnpur by six wickets in a CAB league first division match on Thursday.

